TS_CONFIG(3)                                                                                       tslib                                                                                      TS_CONFIG(3)

NAME
       ts_config, ts_reconfig - read tslib's configuration

SYNOPSIS
       #include <tslib.h>

       int ts_config(struct tsdev *dev);

       int ts_reconfig(struct tsdev *dev);

DESCRIPTION
       ts_config()  loads  and  initialises all modules configured in the tslib configuration file TSLIB_CONFFILE , see ts.conf (5).  ts_reconfig() re-runs ts_config and updates the configuration if the
       configuration file has changed.

RETURN VALUE
       Zero is returned on success. A negative value is returned in case of an error.

SEE ALSO
       ts_read(3), ts_open(3), ts_setup(3), ts_close(3), ts.conf(5)

